"34:6:4" : {s: 34, a: 6, w: 4, r: "علم", t: "ٱلْعِلْمَ", l: "عِلْم", lc: 105, tl: "l-ʿil'ma", lb: "জ্ঞান",e: "the knowledge", b: "", i: "ilmu", f: 10, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
